desc:
Vertical shafts are seen here and there along the sides of this underground
road. They are about five hundred feet apart and square, six feet on a side;
there is no telling how far down they go. Each is surrounded by a granite curb;
on some such, metal mounts for lifts or hoists are still to be seen. Such
appliances have been removed or destroyed, and there is no way to descend. From
one shaft comes a faint whiff of rotting flesh.
